# Supply-chain hygiene: refuse packages published within the last ~7 days,
# where freshly-published malicious versions are most often caught and yanked.
# npm has no rolling "minimum release age", so this pins a static cutoff date.
# Bump it forward periodically to keep a ~7-day-old snapshot (set 2026-05-29 on 2026-06-05).
before=2026-05-29
